 As needed/demanded for this study, this income ability to stretch differs/changes with the level of 
 income and becomes negative when incomes increase to the point whereÂ· 
 the expression b jY is less than c. Ito et al. (1989) used thin slice, 
 time-series analysis to guess income elasticities of demand for the PRC 
 and 13 other Asian countries. Their results pointed to/showed that the income 
 ability to stretch of demand in the PRC (lowered in number/got worse/gotten worse) from 0.42 in 1961 to 0.13 in 1984. 
 In this study, time-series data are used to carefully study the relationship and 
 different price (numbers that change/things that change) from the ones used by Ito et al. (1989) are 
 included. Also, human consumption is used as the dependent 
 (number or thing that changes) rather than total disappearance as in the study by Ito et al. (1989). 
 Aside from human consumption, the principal use of rice is for animals 
 feed. Over 90% of the meat ate/destroyed in the PRC is pork although (related to chickens, hens, turkeys, etc.) 
 and dairy production are also significant animals businesses/projects (World Bank, 
 1987). Industrial animals production based on scientifically compounded 
 
