 PROJECTIONS OF CHINESE RICE CONSUMPTION 
 
 The first step in projecting human rice consumption in China is to 
 develop (statements about the future) of the likely (change over time) of real income. Real per person 
 income has grown at an average once-a-year rate of about 7% in the 1980's. 
 These high rates of growth are not likely to be sustained in the 1990's. 
 Fast money-based growth over the last few years has led to inflationary pressures 
 and the government is working to slow growth rates. For the purposes of 
 
